= Install ROS =&#xd;
&#xd;
----&#xd;
&#xd;
1. After installing and conﬁguring Ubuntu as a virtual machine, you can start installing ROS.&#xd;
1. Start virtual machine and open a new terminal using **[Ctrl]** +** [Alt] **+ **T.**&#xd;
1. First you have to update the source list or add a new source. The following command is executed in the terminal:(% class="box infomessage" %)&#xd;
(((&#xd;
        $ sudo sh -c 'echo "deb http:~/~/packages.ros.org/ros/ubuntu $(lsb_release -sc) main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ros-latest.list' &#xd;
)))&#xd;
1. In the next step, the key of the foreign source is added to the keybund.(% class="box infomessage" %)&#xd;
(((&#xd;
    $ sudo apt-key adv ~-~-keyserver hkp:~/~/ha.pool.sks-keyservers.net:80 ~-~-recv-key 421C365BD9FF1F717815A3895523BAEEB01FA116&#xd;
)))&#xd;
1. Before the installation of ROS begins, it is ensured that the system is up-to-date and the new source will be considered. This is done with:(% class="box infomessage" %)&#xd;
(((&#xd;
    $ sudo apt-get update&#xd;
)))&#xd;
1. ROS includes a variety of packages, tools and libraries, so it is advisable to choose a default installation for the beginning. The following command will download and install an extensive ROS Version(((&#xd;
(% class="box infomessage" %)&#xd;
(((&#xd;
    $ sudo apt-get update&#xd;
)))&#xd;
)))&#xd;
1. (((&#xd;
To be able to use ROS you have to initialize rosdep . This makes it easy to determine system commitments during compilation and is needed for various core components of ROS.&#xd;
&#xd;
(((&#xd;
(% class="box infomessage" %)&#xd;
(((&#xd;
    $ sudo apt-get update&#xd;
)))&#xd;
)))&#xd;
&#xd;
(((&#xd;
    $ sudo apt-get update&#xd;
)))&#xd;
&#xd;
(((&#xd;
(% class="box warningmessage" %)&#xd;
(((&#xd;
~> Attention! Do not execute rosdep update with root-privileges!&#xd;
\\ ```bash&#xd;
     $ rosdep update&#xd;
 ```&#xd;
)))&#xd;
)))&#xd;
)))&#xd;
1. (((&#xd;
The following command adds the ROS environment variables directly to the bash source so that they are directly available in each new bash.&#xd;
To make the change eﬀective, the source of the current Bash is re-selected:&#xd;
&#xd;
(% class="box infomessage" %)&#xd;
(((&#xd;
    $ echo "source /opt/ros/kinetic/setup.bash" >> ~~/.bashrc&#xd;
)))&#xd;
&#xd;
(((&#xd;
(% class="box infomessage" %)&#xd;
(((&#xd;
    $ source ~~/.bashrc&#xd;
)))&#xd;
)))&#xd;
)))</content>
</xwikidoc>@


